Multiple libraries may be specified as a comma-separated list. Once loaded, libraries are accessed via the google.maps.libraryName namespace.
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/libraries

Map Options:
map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById('map'), {
  center: {lat: -34.397, lng: 150.644},
  zoom: 8
});
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/tutorial

zoom level:
1: World
5: Landmass/continent
10: City
15: Streets
20: Buildings

map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById("map"), {...});

-Constructor
Map(mapDiv:Node, opts?:MapOptions )
-Description
Creates a new map inside of the given HTML container — which is typically a DIV element — using any (optional) parameters that are passed.
https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/tutorial

